<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98269953225175></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98269953225175><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=4&mid=98269953225175>RE: What weapon?</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?id=29939><span id= >tinkle</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>12 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Feb 20th 3:05 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>All 2HS and 2HB for a bard is capped at 1. So I would forget about any 2 hand weapons. Even though you can equip them they will never do you much good.<br><br>The Bard can play many roles even at a mid level. If your primary duty is to buff and heal the group you might want a fast 1HS weapon and a Dagger. This does not attract attention to yourself so your songs don't get interupted as much. It also allows you to hit more often which does several things like interupt the Mob if they are casters and it raises your skill levels faster. If on the other hand you are a tank for the group then a heavier weapon might be a better choice. <br><br>IMHO at higher levels (I am 43 currently) I go for the fast lighter weapons and count on the casters to nuke or warriors to mele the Mob to death while I either buff the team or control the mob.<br><br>These are general guidelines in any case. The members you are grouped with and the target you are after will all dictate the roll you play as a bard. My weapons by the way are the Gleaming Short Sword and the Obsidian Shard. If anyone disagrees with my choices they can feel free to twink me with something better. :^) <br><br>Tinkle LilBelle<br>Bard for www.brambledmoon.com<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
